    <field name="scopecontent_teim">The documents pertain to Bloom's writing of the article and contains drafts of the article, correspondence related to it, and much of the documentation and research used in its writing.</field>
    <field name="bioghist_teim">Bernhard J. Stern (1894-1956) was a social scientist and political radical who came under persecution from Congressional investigative committees during the McCarthy period. The materials in the collection were assembled by Samuel W. Bloom, a sociology professor who wrote an article on Stern, "The Intellectual in a Time of Crisis," for Volume 26 of the Journal of the History of the Behavioral Sciences.</field>
    <field name="acqinfo_teim">Donated by Jon Bloom in 2008. The accession number associated with this gift is 2008.018.</field>
